## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

- Frameworks: React with TypeScript (or your preferred strongly-typed stack). Use a state management approach suitable for the app (e.g., React Context, Redux Toolkit) for global resort data and user permissions.
- State and Defaults:
  - useState<ResortType[]>([]) for arrays.
  - Initialize components with safe defaults and guards: e.g., const media = resort?.media ?? [].
- Components composition:
  - ResortDetailPage composes: ResortHeader, TabsNav, OverviewCard, RoomsTable, PoliciesPanel, MediaGallery, ContactsList, InternalNotesPanel.
  - ResortBibleFacade and ResortBibleDirectory are reusable modules with their own small internal state for facet selections and results.
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA attributes for tabs, accordions, and modal dialogs.
  - Keyboard navigable gallery and forms.
- Performance:
  - Lazy-load heavy sections (Media gallery, large room lists) using React.lazy/Suspense or component-level code splitting.
  - Use virtualization for long lists where applicable.
- Data safety in UI:
  - All fetch results and local computations must guard against null/undefined: e.g., (resort?.rooms ?? []).map(...) guarded by Array.isArray(resort?.rooms).
- UI interactions:
  - Tabs: click-driven with accessible focus states; preserve scroll position per tab.
  - Media lightbox: accessible modal with prev/next navigation.
  - Inline editing: editable fields with optimistic UI updates and error fallback.
- API integration:
  - Centralized API client with a fetch wrapper that ensures: response shape validation, try/catch error handling, and null-safe returns.
  - Use the runtime safety rules for any array/map/filter/reduce operations on API data.

### Backend

- Database schema (schematic):
  - resorts: id, name, location, transferTimes (text[]), kidsPolicy, dining json, seasonality json, media json, etc.
  - rooms: id, resortId, name, image, occupancyAdults, occupancyKids, rateSample, is2Bedroom, description
  - media: id, resortId, type, url, caption, photographer
  - contacts: id, resortId, name, role, email, phone, notes
  - notes: id, resortId, author, text, date, category
  - ratings: id, resortId, score, source, date, comments
  - partners: id, resortId, name, role
  - perks, restrictions, policies: as json fields or related tables
- Endpoints (as above in API Layer) with proper authentication/authorization:
  - RW operations gated by role (Admin > full, Agent/Ops > limited edits, Finance > finance fields).
- Validation:
  - Input validation and sanitization on all create/update endpoints.
  - Return shapes validated by frontend (use data ?? [] patterns on lists).
- Performance:
  - Implement indexed searches for resort fields to support fast faceted search.
  - Paginate large lists (rooms, media, notes) in API responses if needed.

### Integration

- Data flows:
  - Resort Bible data is the source of truth for standard fields; Resort Detail fetches a specific resort by ID and resolves related data (rooms, media, contacts, notes, ratings).
  - Resort Bible Faceted Search consumes the same underlying resort data and returns a filtered set of IDs with summary fields for display in the UI.
  - Directory bulk import/export integrates with a CSV/JSON payload path that maps to the Resort model with proper validation and error reporting.
- Security integration:
  - Authentication and authorization govern access to sensitive sections (Internal Notes, editing fields). Use role-based guards in API and UI.
- Data consistency:
  - All arrays retrieved from APIs must be treated with null-safety as described (data ?? [], Array.isArray checks), especially for mapping/rendering.

---

## User Experience Flow

1) Agent/Ops logs in with proper role.
2) Navigate to Resort Bible > Directory to search/filter resorts with fast facet builder.
3) From Directory, select a resort to view Resort Detail.
4) Resort Detail loads header with resort name, location, and quick tags; tabs present Overview, Rooms, Perks & Policies, Media, Contacts, Internal Notes.
5) In Overview:
   - Read key stats, transfer times, kids policy, dining summary, and seasonality snapshot.
   - See partner badges and quick actions (Check Availability, Propose Itinerary, Create Task).
6) In Rooms:
   - View Room Types table with images, occupancy, rates, and 2-bedroom flag; potential drill-down to room detail.
7) In Perks & Policies:
   - Review dining options, transfer expectations, restrictions, minimum stays; edit if permitted.
8) In Media:
   - Interact with gallery; open lightbox to view images/videos; captions visible; upload new media if permitted.
9) In Contacts:
   - See supplier contacts; connect to bookings; call/email actions available.
10) In Internal Notes:
    - Review panel notes and ratings; add/edit notes if permitted; audit trail visible.
11) Use Resort Bible Faceted Search to identify fast matches (e.g., kids friendly + <45 min transfer + beach + 2-bedroom suites) and navigate back to Directory or Resort Detail.
12) Use Bulk Import/Export for Directory management as needed by admin teams.

