## Technical Specifications

Data Models (TypeScript-friendly)
- Resort: as defined earlier
- RoomType, MediaItem, Contact, Rating, Note, etc., as defined above

API Endpoints (Routes & Methods)
- GET /api/resorts/:id
- GET /api/resorts?filters=...
- POST /api/resorts
- PATCH /api/resorts/:id
- GET /api/resorts/:id/rooms
- GET /api/resorts/:id/media
- GET /api/resorts/:id/contacts
- GET /api/resorts/:id/notes
- POST /api/resorts/:id/notes
- POST /api/resorts/bulk-import
- POST /api/resorts/bulk-export

Security
- Role-based access: Admin, Agent, Ops, Finance with granular permissions.
- JWT or session-based authentication with token refresh.
- Input validation on all endpoints; sanitize strings; enforce field-length constraints.

Validation Rules
- All array results must be validated: const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Optional chaining for nested values; avoid direct property access without guards.
- Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.
- Ensure nullish coalescing for API fetch: const resort = data ?? null; handle absence gracefully.

Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Resort Detail page renders all major sections (Header, Tabs, Overview, Rooms, Perks & Policies, Media, Contacts, Internal Notes) with correct data bindings and safe rendering for missing fields.
- [ ] All lists (rooms, media, notes, contacts, partners) render using safe guards: (list ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray(list) checks.
- [ ] Resort Bible Faceted Search returns results that correctly reflect selected facets and handles empty results gracefully ([] when none).
- [ ] Directory bulk import/export supports CSV/JSON payloads with proper validation and error reporting; data mapped to Resort model consistently.
- [ ] All API responses validated on frontend; missing data defaults do not cause runtime errors.
- [ ] UI interactions (lightbox, editing panels, tabs, sort, and filters) work with permission gating and do not crash on partial data.

UI/UX Guidelines

- Follow the provided Visual Style section:
  - Color palette: primary white, olive green accents, warm neutrals, deep charcoal text, soft gold highlights.
  - Typography: Playfair Display/Georgia for headings; Lato/Helvetica Neue for body.
  - Card design: subtle shadows, 4-8px radius, dividers, hover lift.
  - Navigation: sticky header, underline active state, responsive behavior with a mobile nav.
  - Micro-interactions: restrained hover/focus transitions, consistent with luxury aesthetic.
- Accessibility: ensure keyboard navigation, screen-reader friendly labels, color-contrast compliance.

