## Notes on Implementation Nuances

- Ensure all interaction points that read arrays from the API guard against null by defaulting to [] and validating with Array.isArray before mapping.
- Use data ?? [] in all Supabase-derived reads to protect against null returns.
- Initialize all React state hooks that store arrays as useState<Type[]>([]) and ensure type-safety across the components.
- When dealing with nested API responses, always use optional chaining and fallback defaults to prevent undefined access errors.
- Structure components to be easily testable and mockable, with clear separation of concerns between data access, presentation, and UI logic.
- Maintain a clean separation between public-facing data (Resort Detail) and internal data (Internal Notes) with appropriate access control.

If you would like, I can generate a concrete folder/file skeleton with TypeScript interfaces, sample React components, and mock API wrappers that follow these constraints, ready to plug into your existing project structure. for style.

